I"ò<p>Rafael Raposo Pires (1994) is a Portuguese visual artist with a postgraduate degree in Multimedia Art (Moving Image) from the Faculty of Fine Arts of the University of Lisbon. His artistic practice consists of performative photographs and videos produced along pedestrian drifts made in various urban spaces and also related to the body: about its movement in a given landscape and the limits of physical wear and tear.<br />
He exhibits regularly since 2018 in Portugal and abroad. In 2022 he was selected for the Vila Franca de Xira Photography Biennial, and participated in the artist residencies AiR_Cachopo (PT) and Default 22 (IT). In 2023 he obtained a mobility grant through the Culture Moves Europe program, funded by the European Union.</p>
